<HEADLINE> Mudslide Flattens Power Station  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BEIJING (AP) -- Rescuers in southwest China are searching for
workers who have been missing since a mudslide destroyed a power
station last week, killing 14 people and injuring 27 others, the
state-run Xinhua News Agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The mudslide, which happened on Aug. 13 in Yingjiang county,
Yunnan province, leveled the power station, which had 45 workers
inside, Xinhua said.
</P>
<P>
   Rescuers were still searching for the four missing workers, the
news agency said. The disaster caused an estimated $2.4 million in
damages, it said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
