<HEADLINE> Man shot to death after bar fight; police chase car after shooting  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) - A bar fight apparently led to the fatal
shooting of an Albany man early Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Vraden Branch, 45, was shot multiple times in the chest around
4:52 a.m. and walked several steps before collapsing, police said.
</P>
<P>
   When police responded to the scene, they chased a car that was
speeding away from the shooting. One man got out of the car and
began running with a 9mm handgun. He was caught and is in police
custody, though he has not been charged.
</P>
<P>
   Branch had argued with several men in a city bar, police said.
The same men allegedly spotted Branch walking, and one got out of
the car and shot him, according to police.
</P>
<P>
   Branch was pronounced dead at Albany Medical Center.
</P>
