</P>
<P>
   HRC: ''The Prodigal Son'' (Henri J.M. Nouwen)
</P>
<P>
   ---
</P>
<P>
   FAVORITE MUSIC OR ART:
</P>
<P>
   RL: I love all music, but I guess if I had to choose a favorite
it would be Blues. In terms of art, I love marine paintings and
Hudson River valley paintings.
</P>
<P>
   HRC: Sculpture.
</P>
<P>
   ---
</P>
<P>
   WHAT's SOMETHING YOU LEARNED BEING A PARENT? ...AND SOMETHING
YOU WOULD TELL AN EXPECTANT OR NEW PARENT?
</P>
<P>
   RL: Patience. ... Relish the moments with your children when
they're small.
</P>
<P>
   HRC: No matter how much you love your child, your job is to help
that little person turn into an independent self-sufficient man or
woman. You cannot control the outcome of their lives. You've got to
give them the love, the guidance, the attention, the discipline and
support every child deserves to have, but at the end of the day he
or she is a separate person.
</P>
<P>
