<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mets 9, Dodgers 6  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Edgardo Alfonzo, Lenny Harris and Bubba
Trammell homered and the New York Mets turned two Los Angeles
errors into three eighth-inning runs in a 9-6 victory Sunday over
the Dodgers.
</P>
<P>
   The Mets, who remained 1&AMP;frac12; games behind first-place Atlanta in
the NL East, won their eighth straight series.
</P>
<P>
   Mike Bordick and Darryl Hamilton singled to open the eighth.
Bordick was trapped off third on Harris' comebacker to Terry Adams
(5-6), but he and pinch-runner Joe McEwing scored when the throw by
third baseman Adrian Beltre sailed over catcher Todd Hundley's
head.
</P>
<P>
   Harris scored when Derek Bell's routine grounder went through
the legs of second baseman Mark Grudzielanek for the Dodgers' third
error of the game and sixth in the three-game series.
</P>
<P>
   Turk Wendell (6-4) pitched two innings for the victory, allowing
a run and three hits. Armando Benitez pitched the ninth for his
33rd save in 37 chances.
</P>
<P>
   Eric Karros gave the Dodgers a 5-4 lead with an RBI single that
chased starter Bobby J. Jones in the fifth. But Trammell and Harris
opened the sixth with consecutive home runs against Darren
Dreifort.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers, who overcame a 4-0 deficit, tied it 6-6 in the
seventh when Gary Sheffield scored from first on Shawn Green's
bloop single to left-center that was misplayed twice by left
fielder Harris.
</P>
<P>
   Dreifort, who won his previous six starts, was charged with six
runs -- five earned -- and seven hits in five-plus innings.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers closed to 4-3 in the third when Sheffield scored on
Green's RBI double. Los Angeles got even on Hundley's 21st homer
and second of the game. It was the 12th time Hundley has homered
twice in a game and second this season.
</P>
<P>
   Alfonzo opened the scoring with his 16th homer after a
ground-rule double by Bell. Alfonzo had 13 hits, 10 RBIs, three
homers and a .361 average against the Dodgers this season.
</P>
<P>
   The Mets made it 4-0 in the second. Jay Payton led off with a
double and one out later, Jones swung at a third strike, that
Hundley couldn't handle cleanly, and reached base on the passed
ball.
</P>
<P>
   Harris followed with an RBI single that sent Jones to third.
Harris stole second and Hundley's throw went into center field,
allowing Jones to score.
</P>
<P>
   Hundley was booed loudly when he came to bat in the bottom of
the inning after a one-out single by Karros. But he silenced the
crowd of 46,122 by driving a 1-1 pitch into the right field bullpen
to close the deficit to 4-2.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Hundley helped the Dodgers join Atlanta as the only NL
teams this season to have four players with at least 20 homers. ...
Grudzielanek has 100 stolen bases in 131 attempts. ... The Mets
have stranded an NL-leading 949 baserunners, including seven on
Sunday. ... Hundley, who broke Roy Campanella's major league record
for homers by a catcher in 1996 with the Mets, homered twice
against Philadelphia on May 26. ... Mets C Mike Piazza made the
defensive play of the game in the second inning, racing back to the
home-plate screen and making a diving grab of Alex Cora's popup.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
