<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-20 20:04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Padres 5, Expos 4  </HEADLINE>
By BERNIE WILSON
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Jay Witasick hit two run-scoring singles -- his
first two big league hits and RBIs -- to help himself to his first
victory with San Diego as the Padres beat the Montreal Expos 5-4 on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Witasick, obtained from Kansas City on July 31 for right-hander
Brian Meadows, singled in the second and third innings, both
following intentional walks to Wiki Gonzalez. His second single
capped the four-run third, in which only one run was earned because
of first baseman Lee Stevens' error.
</P>
<P>
   Witasick, who spent his first 4&AMP;frac12; seasons in the American League,
was 0-for-16 coming into the game.
</P>
<P>
   He was pulled after allowing Jose Vidro's two-run homer in the
seventh that pulled the Expos to 5-4. Vidro, who went 3-for-4,
homered for the second straight game and has 20 on the season.
</P>
<P>
   Witasick (1-1) pitched 6 1-3 innings, allowing four runs, three
earned, and 10 hits while striking out seven and walking two.
</P>
<P>
   Trevor Hoffman pitched 1 1-3 innings for his 33rd save in 39th
opportunities. He came on with a runner on first and two outs in
the eighth and struck out Fernando Seguignol.
</P>
<P>
   The Expos have lost nine of 10.
</P>
<P>
   Montreal took a 1-0 lead in the second on Brian Schneider's RBI
double and the Padres tied it in the bottom of the inning when
Witasick hit an opposite-filed single to right with two outs to
score Bret Boone, aboard on a leadoff single.
</P>
<P>
   The Padres scored four runs on four hits and an error in the
third. With runners on first and second and one out, Stevens let
Boone's grounder roll under his glove for an error, allowing Ryan
Klesko to score from second. John Mabry hit an RBI double, Ruben
Rivera had an RBI groundout and after Gonzalez again was
intentionally walked, Witasick singled to center to score Mabry.
</P>
<P>
   Expos starter Felipe Lira (3-3) lasted just three innings,
allowing five runs, two earned, on six hits while walking three. He
was making just his second start of the year, taking Mike Johnson's
place in the rotation.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Vidro tied Mike Lansing's 1997 club record for most homers
by a second baseman. ... The Padres finished 5-4 against the Expos,
just the second time in 11 seasons they've won the season series.
... Lira went longer in his last appearance, four innings of relief
against San Francisco on Tuesday night, than he did in Sunday's
start. He also lost against San Francisco.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-08-20-00 2004 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000820.0099 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-20 20:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Miller Pulls Out of Olympic Trials  </HEADLINE>
By EDDIE PELLS
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON (AP) -- Two-time Olympian Shannon Miller pulled out of the
Olympic gymnastic trials Sunday after jamming her knees on her
opening vault.
</P>
<P>
   Miller said there was ''really no injury,'' but no reason to
continue either, because of the pain that overtook her legs when
they jammed into the mat after a roundoff back-flip with a half
turn.
</P>
<P>
   Her coach, Steve Nunno, decided it was better to have her drop
out and see if national team coordinator Bela Karolyi would choose
her based on what little he has seen, rather than try to compete
with her legs growing stiff and clearly not at 100 percent.
</P>
<P>
   ''I made an executive decision to pull out,'' Nunno said. ''In
my mind, it was the obvious thing to do when you look at it from a
strategic standpoint.''
</P>
<P>
   Miller said doctors gave her clearance to continue with the
meet, but she agreed with Nunno's decision to pull out.
</P>
<P>
   ''They've seen what I can do,'' she said. ''At this point,
health is more important. I can be ready to go in two days if they
decide I'm needed.''
</P>
<P>
   If she is, it would almost certainly be for her expertise on the
uneven bars, where she scored a 9.650 at nationals and a 9.712 here
Friday in the first round of trials.
</P>
<P>
   Everything else seems like a big guess.
</P>
<P>
   Miller, who has won a record seven Olympic medals, pulled out of
nationals after that single bars routine to let the hairline crack
in her lower right leg continue to heal. On the first day of
trials, her bars routine was the only one that drew over a 9.30,
although Nunno felt Miller was underscored by the judges.
</P>
<P>
   Her last chance to impress came Sunday, but that ended quickly.
</P>
<P>
   After walking gingerly off the mat, she decided to attempt her
second vault. Her landing was awkward there, too, and she came off
limping, fighting back tears. Nunno had to help her down the stairs
and back down the runway.
</P>
<P>
   They went to the training room shortly after. Miller returned to
the floor and grabbed her warmup suit, then headed over to the
uneven bars, where she was supposed to compete next.
</P>
<P>
   But there would be no more for Miller, who could barely walk.
</P>
<P>
   Miller scored an 8.650 for the vaults, nowhere near what she
would need to improve her standing, even though scores aren't the
determining factor in who makes the six-person Olympic team.
</P>
<P>
   Miller is the second member of the 1996 team to pull out this
week. Dominique Moceanu scratched before the trials began because
of a floating bone chip in her right knee.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-08-20-00 2008 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000820.0100 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-20 20:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 7 Arrested in Venezuelan Drug Bust  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) -- Venezuelan forces seized five tons of
cocaine and arrested at least seven people in a remote jungle
region in the eastern coast during the country's largest drug bust
to date, authorities said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The raid, which took place Friday, was the result of a six-month
investigation financed by the U.S. Drug Enforcement Agency. The
National Guard recovered 173 packages of cocaine about to be
shipped to Europe, National Guard Officer Eduardo Sanchez told The
Associated Press.
</P>
<P>
   Agents are still in pursuit of at least two suspected leaders of
the Los Mellizos drug ring who fled into the Orinoco jungle during
a gun battle that preceded the raid.
</P>
<P>
   The probe, known as ''Orinoco 2000,'' used telephone bugging
equipment, more than 200 anti-drug officers, three planes, three
helicopters and eight boats, according to El Universal newspaper
which first reported the bust. Colombia, France, Britain, Italy,
Greece and Panama also collaborated with the operation, the paper
said.
</P>
<P>
   Venezuela is a key trafficking route for Colombian cocaine en
route to the United States and Europe.
</P>
<P>
   President Hugo Chavez's refusal to allow U.S. anti-narcotic
flights over Venezuelan airspace on grounds of protecting
''national sovereignty'' continues to sour relations between the
two countries. Chavez defends Venezuela's anti-narcotic record,
pointing to successful drug bust operations.
</P>
<P>
   The seven suspects captured in the Orinoco 2000 bust were due to
appear in court in Tucupita, the capital of eastern Delta Amacuro
state, El Universal said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-08-20-00 2012 </TRAILER>
