   ATLANTA: As the Braves' team bus pulled up to Pacific Bell Park
Sunday, a small but vocal faction shouted ''Go home, Rocker!'' in
reference to controversial Atlanta reliever John Rocker. He was
loudly booed when he took the field in the ninth inning. ... Walt
Weiss was 4-for-5 for the Braves. He has been 3-for-24 over his
last 11 games. The last four-hit game for Weiss came Sept. 2, 1997
at Anaheim.
