</P>
<P>
   Victoria Supple, mother of the four kids, was out at breakfast
or she and her boyfriend would have been asleep in that bed, she
told police.
</P>
<P>
   York's three daughters, 5, 9 and 10, were sleeping in one bed
and her 6-year-old son was asleep on the floor when the Chevrolet
Cavalier crashed through the wall. The boy slept through the
commotion.
</P>
