<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-20 22:34 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Love That Red Wins Pat O'Brien  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Love That Red, runner-up in the Bing
Crosby Handicap three weeks ago, got the job done Sunday, winning
the $150,000 Pat O'Brien Handicap at Del Mar by 1&AMP;frac12; lengths over
Cliquot.
</P>
<P>
   Love That Red, ridden by Corey Nakatani and carrying 118 pounds,
went through a narrow opening on the rail turning into the stretch,
then held on, covering seven furlongs in 1:21 4-5.
</P>
<P>
   Love That Red paid $5.20, $3 and $2.40 and earned the winner's
purse of $90,000.
</P>
<P>
   Cliquot returned $3 and $2.40, while Son of a Pistol paid $2.80
to show.
</P>
<P>
   Love That Red, the 8-5 favorite, gave trainer Bob Baffert his
sixth stakes win at the halfway point of the 43-day Del Mar season.
</P>
<P>
   The 4-year-old gelding won for the eighth time in 17 starts.
</P>
</TEXT>
