<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwest Pilot Dies in Flight  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- A pilot flying a Northwest DC-10 died of an
apparent heart attack Sunday, and two other pilots safely landed
the plane, an airline spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
   The pilot slumped over in his seat while en route to Minneapolis
from Los Angeles on Flight 308, said Northwest spokesman Dennis
Mollura.
</P>
<P>
   The pilot was pronounced dead when the plane landed.
</P>
<P>
   The two other pilots in the cockpit took over immediately. It is
standard procedure on a DC-10 to have two other experienced pilots
aboard, Mollura said.
</P>
